node.text: Everyone wants the feeling of freedom, but procrastination can feel like you are caged and can't find the key. We all get stuck in patterns, and the patterns become habits. Procrastination is the same thing.  Procrastination is an action (or non-action) – and it does not define you. Why? It is a habit, that is a behavior pattern that can be changed into a new pattern

node.text:
Imagine that life is like a movie. Not only are you the main character, you are also the writer and director of the script. Remember when schoolyard kids would shout "YOLO" (you only live once) and then do something courageous or silly? You only have one life to live (this time around). Life is challenging you to live it fully. We can face the fear of getting out of our comfort zone, not being”perfect” and focus on doing more of what is meaningful and makes us happy. You are invited to be the main character in your life, not a side character thinking about what you wish your life was like.

So, are you ready? Once you commit to making yourself the major character in your life story, today is the first day of the rest of your life. Today is the day you recognise that you are enough, and that if you want to be more, you can make it happen for yourself. You have nothing to lose. Today is a great day to behave as the person you always wanted to be. Go for it!
#projecthappiness
#mindfulmonday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Say Yes If You Agree!

“What other people think of me is none of my business.” -Wayne Dyer

Realizing the importance of being unapologetically yourself and having the ability to not care at all about other people’s opinions of your decisions as long as you’re happy and passionate about the path you choose to follow is so necessary.

When you let go of the need for justification or acceptance from anybody other than yourself, true confidence emerges. People will convince you to change your mind, but the greatest way to learn is to check in with yourself  and trust your instincts. You must develop experience by allowing yourself to do what your heart tells you to do. Sometimes all it takes is a simple ‘yes’ or ‘no’ answer – no explanation needed. The sooner you learn to let go of the idea that you need other people’s approval, the happier and better off you’ll be
#projecthappiness
#soulsunday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 21, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'When you stop expecting people to be perfect, you can like them for who they are. Donald Miller @projecthappinessorg @proje othap'.

node.text:
The truth is, people are messy. Fears, worries, eccentricities, stressful habits, hang-ups - it's part of being human. Everyone you meet is most likely dealing with a challenge at home or at work that is affecting them. Much of it is beneath the surface, and we may never know. Sometimes they don’t know themselves, and that’s OKAY. 

Where we get stuck is in expecting others to be perfect, or expecting perfection from ourselves. 

A) That’s impossible. We are designed to GROW! 
B) Try to release expectation and substitute some appreciation. Notice that  life gets so much easier. 
C) When we can accept ourselves fully (flaws and all) and accept that we are ALL works in process, then we can look to what is amazing, delightful, lovely and brilliant in each and every person, & resonate on that frequency. 

Self judgment (don’t do it!) and judgement of others (redirect!) are rooted in fear.

Instead:
Embrace yourself for who you are.
Celebrate others for their strengths rather than ruminate on what annoys you.
Life will be so much lighter...
#projecthappiness
#positivity
#socialsaturday

node.text:
Did you know that you may not fully realize the influence that you have on others around you? Some small act of kindness that you thought nothing of, may have planted seeds in another person in ways you could not possibly see. You may have given them hope when they were downhearted, the sense of being seen, or even a reason to push on.  A sincere thank you, a warm hello can be powerful medicine. This is not for anything in return; you may never know if your intentions landed... and that’s OK. 

One thing you can be sure of is that whether it is obvious or not, emotions are contagious. When we acknowledge, even by a warm smile, the good in others, and treat them as if that is the only thing we see, they receive an energetic boost to reconnect with the best within them.

Kindness is a FORCE driven by love, empathy and compassion. And the giver benefits at least as much as the person on the receiving end. Let's make it a priority to brighten someone's day , and see how our own lives change as a result.. After all, we’re all in this together…

 CHALLENGE: in the next 24 hours, lay some kindness onto someone you may not know well, OR someone you know intimately who could use a little love. Notice how YOU feel, and how long that feeling brightens your day. Send a thumbs up if you are willing to try.
#projecthappiness
#thoughtfulthursday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Choose to focus on all that you are, instead of all that you are not. Unknown @projecthappiness_org'.

node.text:
What you focus on grows. We always have choices. Focus on what brings you misery (you may actually feel your body contract), or focus on what makes you feel lighter and more expansive. 

Think of what comes naturally to you, what you love to do, what puts you in a state of flow. Remember situations when you felt at your best. These feelings are still in your cellular memory - you can call them up to help you change your state.

Know that the ego mind will want to remind you of all you are not - not good enough, ready enough, talented enough… you know the drill. It takes vigilance to catch those patterns in play. But you can. 

And then change your focus to what supports your growth. “I always find my way, I can figure it out, I can do hard things, etc.”

This is a practice, and the more you intentionally switch gears, the more your brain builds new neural pathways to support you. You are much more expansive than your ego would have you believe. Focus on what calls you and take one step to reach it.  Action builds self-trust. You got this. Focus on all that you are.

Say YES if  you are ready to stop focusing on the disempowering messages your ego mind is feeding you.
#projecthappiness
#wellnesswednesday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Accept all of the things in your life that you regret; they happened, and they aren't going to change. What you can embrace and value about them, though, is the ripple effect they have throughout your life. You have learned some important lessons, particularly in these circumstances.Those lessons, based on your experience, are molding you into the person you are now, and will also be the basis from which you give advice to others. 

The wonderful feelings of happiness that good days provide, the intense experiences that bad days bring, the lessons of your worst days, and the memories of your best days are all valuable.  They're shaping you into the person you are and will become. Live every day with absolute gratitude, respect, love and care because this is life and it will test you forever and a day.  Love your life; you are here for a reason.

Give a Heart if you are ready to accept all aspects of your life.
#projecthappiness
#gratituesday
#positivity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'A Life is 10% what happens to you and 90% how you react to to it. Charles R. Swindoll @projecthappiness org designed by freepik'.

node.text:
Life can come at us at times, and there are so many things we cannot control. The difference in forging forward or feeling stuck has a lot to do with the narrative we create around what has happened. In other words, how we INTERPRET the events in our lives. Blaming is natural, often that’s the first way we deal with hurt. But that puts us in more of a victim mode, when our thoughts and fears can seem to take over. But it doesn’t have to be that way.

“The one thing you can’t take away from me is the way I choose to respond to what you do to me. The last of one’s freedoms is to choose one’s attitude in any given circumstance.”― Viktor E. Frankl

That is not to say, deny what you have been through or just shove it under a rock and pretend, “It’s all good.” Feel what you feel, and have some tools to come back to yourself (breathwork, yoga, walking…) When you recognize that the negative ego is constantly giving you messages of doubt and fear, CHOOSE to remind yourself of who you really are: empowered, stronger and always more aware.
#projecthappiness
#mindfulmonday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
"The time to relax is when you don't have time for it." — Sydney J. Harris
It might be tough to find the time to simply relax in today's fast-paced world. What if I told you that relaxing protects your heart, improves your memory, and reduces your chance of stroke? Isn't it possible that you'll be able to fit it into your schedule then? There are so many health benefits of relaxation, and the truth of the matter is that you'll actually improve your productivity and life quality by allowing yourself the time to sit back and do nothing. Mind-wandering has proven benefits, including helping you return to a place where you can access your intuition.

So, if you've been looking for an excuse to ignore all of your responsibilities and spend the day doing nothing but having fun, this is the day for you. Guilt-free. You are the smart one. Taking a break is not only a lovely thing to do for yourself, but it is also a necessary thing to do for yourself. You'll require it. Don’t allow yourself to run on empty. Replenish your energy, ignite your creativity, and remember who you really are.

Challenge: Before you go to sleep, when you are in a relaxed state, ask yourself, or even your higher self, to give you some insights on an issue you are facing. Whether in the shower, or at unexpected moments, be open to receive hints, clues and signs the following day. 
#projecthappiness
#soulsunday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Real love is not transactional - “I’ll do this for you if you do this for me.” It involves looking through the outer appearances of a person, through their mannerisms, and through the surface affects which really don’t define them. Imagine you had X-ray vision and you can see down to the essence of a person, to their goodness, their vulnerabilities, their hopes and their dreams. 

Love understands that we all carry baggage from the past, and that’s part of being human. And in spite of all that, (and sometimes because of it), we emerge, we shift and we grow. Love is looking for that part, and cheering each other on. As the saying goes, we are all souls in human bodies. When we relate on that level, we cannot help but want the best for one another. Why? We are operating from the frequency of love. 

Send a HEART <3 if you are willing to live more from the frequency of love.
#projecthappiness
#positivity
#socialsaturday
